<GUIClass name="CMUI_DotMatrixBaseForm" id="4a40f388-980e-46b3-a7ff-d9f0a307034d">
    <superclass name="Form"/>
    <transient/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>The concept is that we present a series of labels on a basic form and re-position and re-size
the labels to represent the area of a pre-printed that we can populate with text.
We set the font and font size and gather teh textual strings that we want to put in the label.
We process each label using getTextExtent, and establish where each piece of text should print
relative to the left and top of the page, and add transient objects representing each to an
ordered dictionary.
Rather than use the print frame mechanism which would not work on a dot matrix, we simply print
each textual string in order from its start position. </text>
